      "id": "your-starting-faction",
      "label": "Your starting faction",
      "chooser": "player",
      "prompt": "The player picks the faction they begin entangled with — it colors their first read of the crisis. Each option's detail is the DM's playbook for that faction (leader, seat, claim, the inner-circle agenda, the strength, the fatal flaw, the player's entanglement); all three are equally complex and equally compromised.",
      "options": [
        {
          "id": "iron-circle",
          "name": "The Iron Circle",
          "description": "Start entangled with the military faction. Disciplined, honorable, but brittle — one betrayal could shatter them. You'll see the succession crisis as a soldier first.",
          "detail": "THE IRON CIRCLE — Maredon's army, seated in the Arsenal; the realm was won by the sword and the Circle believes it must be held by one. Their leader is Marshal Edran Hask, Lord-Commander of the garrison — a genuinely honorable soldier who loves the realm more than any claimant, which is exactly what his inner circle counts on: some of his officers would rather have a military stewardship (a junta in all but name) than crown anyone, and they are steering the Marshal toward it without his quite seeing. Strength: discipline, and the only organized armed force inside the walls. Fatal flaw: the Circle's cohesion is honor-bound and therefore brittle — one proven betrayal could crack it down the middle. The player begins as one of Hask's own — an officer, an aide, a sworn sword — trusted, and about to learn what that trust costs."
        },
        {
          "id": "gilded-compact",
          "name": "The Gilded Compact",
          "description": "Start among the merchant coalition. They treat the crown as a business acquisition. You'll see the succession crisis through ledgers, leverage, and backroom deals.",
          "detail": "THE GILDED COMPACT — the merchant houses, seated in the Exchange and the Customs House; they made Vantis the richest port on the coast and they treat the crown as an asset to be acquired. Their First Factor is Sora Coress, who holds the debts of half the nobility and most of the Iron Circle's suppliers, and who is the cleverest person in any room she enters. Her public claim is stability — a crowned king is good for trade — but her inner circle's private arithmetic is uglier: some Compact houses would sell the river-mouth to the foreign power at the border outright, if the price cleared. Strength: money, leverage, and leverage over the people with the leverage. Fatal flaw: the Compact has no loyalty beyond profit; it will defect the instant the math changes, including on the player. The player begins inside the Compact — a factor, an agent, a holder of someone's marker — useful, and being used."
        },
        {
          "id": "hallowed-see",
          "name": "The Hallowed See",
          "description": "Start within the religious order. They believe divine mandate chooses the ruler. You'll see the succession crisis as a matter of faith and prophecy.",
          "detail": "THE HALLOWED SEE — the church that anointed Maredon's first king and every one since; no coronation is valid without it, which makes the See the kingmaker even with no army and no treasury. Its head is Mother Serel, the Pontifex — old, shrewd, and certain that the gods, not the factions, choose the ruler; she is 'interpreting' the prophecies, and which claimant they favor shifts with her reading. Her inner circle is split: some clerics believe Caedran's death and the throne's troubles are divine judgment on the whole royal line, and that Maredon should have NO king — a theocracy under the See. Strength: legitimacy itself; the anointing is the one thing neither money nor swords can counterfeit. Fatal flaw: the schism within over what the prophecy means, and the zealotry of those who would sooner burn the throne than crown a sinner. The player begins of the faith — a cleric, an acolyte, a sworn lay-servant — close to Serel, and about to be asked to read the gods' will a particular way."
        }
      ]
    }
